:wave: :bar_chart: CICD Updates!
Hi there!
So it's been a fun few weeks on the RelEng side, and we've been dealing with several unplanned incidents and efforts on various fronts - but we've still be getting a couple fun things done!

First up: Telemetry updates! The OpenTelemetry Plugin in Jenkins was updated recently to make life much easier when trying to add custom attributes to telemetry data coming out of our pipelines - particularly being able to do things like:
```pipeline {
    options {
        withSpanAttributes([
          spanAttribute(key: 'ib.stack.tenant.id', value: TENANT_ID, target: 'PIPELINE_ROOT_SPAN'),
          spanAttribute(key: 'ib.stack.legacy_build', value: LEGACY_SVC_BUILD, target: 'PIPELINE_ROOT_SPAN'),
        ])
    }
}```
This allows us to build things like this Stack Deployment State (https://grafana.cicd.instabase.com/goto/GadPygwIR?orgId=1) dashboard, allowing us to see at a glance if one or more stacks has been consistently building and deploying properly, failing, rendered unstable, etc. It will hopefully help reduce questions of "this stack failed to deploy - did something change recently?" by making it easy to see if the stack was already unstable / failing prior. :slightly_smiling_face:

You can also click on any given "state box" in the panel and it will give you a direct link to that stack's Deployment Manager GUI! We'll add more drill-down links as we get more and better data collected. :+1:

*Note:* There's a gap in the data, a result of the confluence of "Cody had to fix data collection and dropped some broken bits" and "all the builds are failing because of an unrelated service dependency breakage upstream" :smile: It should be more consistent going forward.
